<subSubSection id="8C8E6575FF4A6AF5FD2A9D351A6DB715" pageId="177" pageNumber="939" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="C42B36FEFF4A6AF5FD2A9D351A6DB715" blockId="177.[725,1316,2805,3229]" pageId="177" pageNumber="939">
Subgenus Pizonyx; 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF4A6AF5FC1D9D351A4FB0BB" baseAuthorityName="E. Geoffroy" baseAuthorityYear="1806" box="[993,1103,2924,2953]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Myotis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="177" pageNumber="939" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="albescens">albescens</taxonomicName>
species group. 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF4A6AF5FD2B9DD61DD3B082" authorityName="G. S. Miller" authorityYear="1898" box="[727,979,2959,2992]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Myotis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="177" pageNumber="939" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="peninsularis">Myotis peninsularis</taxonomicName>
has been considered a subspecies of 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF4A6AF5FC5F9DEF1A24B0E5" baseAuthorityName="J. A. Allen" baseAuthorityYear="1890" box="[931,1060,2998,3031]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Myotis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="177" pageNumber="939" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="velifer">M. velifer</taxonomicName>
, but morphology and mitochondrial phylogeny suggest it is a distinct species. Monotypic.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
